 {"id":"bd-4810","title":"Implement shutdown progress indicator","description":"## Task: Shutdown Progress Indicator

### Parent Feature
Phase 3: Advanced Output Components (bd-1lkf)

### Overview
Create a visual progress indicator for graceful shutdown that shows connection draining, background task completion, and resource cleanup stages.

### Background & Reasoning
Graceful shutdown is critical for production applications but can be confusing without feedback:
- Users wonder if the app is hung or actually shutting down
- Without progress, operators may force-kill and lose in-flight requests
- Visibility into active connections helps debug shutdown hangs
- Resource cleanup stages provide debugging info

### Technical Implementation

#### Data Structures
```rust
// crates/fastapi-output/src/components/shutdown_progress.rs

pub struct ShutdownProgress {
    pub stage: ShutdownStage,
    pub active_connections: usize,
    pub pending_tasks: usize,
    pub resources_to_cleanup: Vec<ResourceCleanup>,
    pub timeout_seconds: u64,
    pub elapsed_seconds: u64,
}

pub enum ShutdownStage {
    SignalReceived,
    StopAccepting,
    DrainingConnections,
    WaitingForTasks,
    CleaningResources,
    Complete,
}

pub struct ResourceCleanup {
    pub name: String,
    pub status: CleanupStatus,
}

pub enum CleanupStatus {
    Pending,
    InProgress,
    Complete,
    Failed(String),
}

pub struct ShutdownDisplay {
    show_spinner: bool,
    show_resource_details: bool,
    update_interval_ms: u64,
}
```

